liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Is there another Carlton miracle left in the Blues' locker? Or are the Lions on the way to a grand final? We're about to find out.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 20': The final quarter is underway

children.content: Is there another Carlton miracle left in the Blues' locker? Or are the Lions on the way to a grand final?

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's right there for Brisbane. The grand final is just one quarter away. But Carlton are still there, still fighting, still trying to make this quarter the toughest of Brisbane's season. There was a moment early in that third term when it felt like the Lions were ready to finish the job, to put the foot firmly on the Blues' throat and run away with the win. But that decisive blow never came. The Blues didn't muster a response of their own, but they hung around. It's been brave, but it'll be for nothing if it doesn't result in goals in the last quarter. It all comes down to this. The Magpies await.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 3QT: Lions kick out to a 20-point lead
